The paper deals with decision-making in uncertain environments, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of game theory concepts and the comparison with existing algorithms suggest that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of computational game theory (cs.GT). The use of mathematical programming and linear programming problems is a central aspect of the paper, which could place it in the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with decentralized decision-making, which could also make it relevant to the sub-category of robotics (cs.RO).
